.jumbotron.jumbotron--projects
  .container
    h1 Projects
    p Here you can find a list of the projects I've worked on. For more in-depth information, you can check out my GitHub profile where I publish most of my code.
.container.projects-list
  ul
    li
      .header
        span.title My LoL Fantasy
        span.cta-github: a.fa.fa-share-square-o(href='https://github.com/PeteyPii/MyLoLFantasy', title='Project link')
        span.time November 2014 &ndash; November 2019
      .subheader
        span.languages JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3, SQL
      ul
        li Web app I made with my friends at a UWaterloo hackathon
        li The app tracks you and your friends' stats in League of Legends games and compares them in a Fantasy-esque system
        li ExpressJS web server renders #[a(href='http://jade-lang.com/') jade] templates for client requests
        li User and statistic data is persisted in a #[a(href='http://www.postgresql.org/') PostgreSQL] database
        li #[a(href='http://redis.io/') Redis] is used to cache session data and #[a(href='https://developer.riotgames.com/') Riot Games API] requests

    li
      .header
        span.title Personal Website
        span.cta-github: a.fa.fa-share-square-o(href='https://github.com/PeteyPii/PersonalWebsite', title='Project link')
        span.time July 2014 &ndash; Present
      .subheader
        span.languages JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3
      ul
        li Website I created to showcase my professional career and to gain some web development skills
        li Houses a mini-game I made called #[a(href='/meteorite') Meteorite]
        li Makes use the following frameworks: #[a(href='https://nodejs.org/en/') Node.js] and #[a(href='https://angularjs.org/') AngularJS]

    li
      .header
